        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Arch pain, also known as arch strain, involves inflammation and/or a burning sensation at the arch of the foot. Various factors can cause arch pain, including structural imbalances or foot injuries. The most common cause of arch pain is Plantar Fasciitis, a condition affecting the plantar fascia, a fibrous tissue band running from the heel to the forefoot.<br/><br/>If untreated and strain on the longitudinal arch continues, a heel spur, a bony protrusion, may develop. Prompt treatment is essential to prevent the condition from worsening.<br/><br/><br/><br/></p>",
